        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 5:34PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Floriston, or near Boca Reservoir, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rainfall, and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Ponding of water on roadways. Minor hail
damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boca Reservoir, Stampede Reservoir, Verdi, Mogul, Floriston,
Hirschdale, Dog Valley, Verdi-Mogul, Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp,
Truckee, Boca Rest Campground, Logger Campground, and Boca
Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
